TCS-style Tricks with ASCII

Check if character is uppercase or lowercase:

c = 'G'
if 65 <= ord(c) <= 90:
    print("Uppercase")
elif 97 <= ord(c) <= 122:
    print("Lowercase")


Convert lowercase to uppercase or vice versa:

c = 'g'
upper = chr(ord(c) - 32)  # 'G'

c = 'G'
lower = chr(ord(c) + 32)  # 'g'


Check if character is digit:

c = '7'
if 48 <= ord(c) <= 57:
    print("Digit")
